column11:
  The object of the present paper is to study of radius of convexity two
certain integral operators as follows \begin{equation*}
  F(z):=\int_{0}^{z}\prod_{i=1}^{n}\left(f'_i(t)\right)^{\gamma_i}{\rm d}t
\end{equation*} and \begin{equation*}
  J(z):=\int_{0}^{z}\prod_{i=1}^{n}\left(f'_i(t)\right)^{\gamma_i}\prod_{j=1}^{m}
  \left(\frac{g_j(z)}{z}\right)^{\lambda_j}{\rm d}t, \end{equation*} where
$\gamma_i, \lambda_i\in\mathbb{C}$, $f_i$ $(1\leq i\leq n)$ and $g_j$ $(1\leq
j\leq m)$ belong to the certain subclass of analytic functions.
